events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Marcus Mariota threw a 12-yard touchdown pass to Josh Huff with 29 seconds left, and No. 13 Oregon overcame a tenacious effort by Oregon State 36-35 on Friday night in the 117th edition of the Civil War rivalry.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ducks slip past Oregon State at last minute

events.name: Fresno State Bulldogs at San Jose State Spartans

headlines.description: David Fales threw for 543 yards and six touchdowns in an entertaining showdown with Derek Carr and San Jose ended No. 16 Fresno State's run toward a possible BCS bowl with a 62-52 victory Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: San Jose State hands Fresno St. its first loss

headlines.description: Jennings rescues No. 17 LSU in 31-27 win over Ark.
headlines.shortLinkText: LSU rallies late after losing Mettenberger

events.name: South Florida Bulls at UCF Knights

headlines.description: Breshad Perriman scored on a 52-yard touchdown pass from Blake Bortles late in the fourth quarter to give No. 19 UCF a 23-20 win over South Florida on Friday night, keeping the Knights on course for a conference title and BCS bid.
headlines.shortLinkText: UCF edges USF to grab share of AAC title

headlines.description: Jake Rudock threw for two touchdowns, including a 24-yarder to Kevonte Martin-Manley right after Iowa had stuffed Nebraska on a fake punt, and the Hawkeyes finished the regular season with a 38-17 victory on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa hands Nebraska 3rd home loss of year

events.name: East Carolina Pirates at Marshall Thundering Herd

headlines.description: akeem Cato threw for two touchdowns and ran for two more on Friday as Marshall took an early undisputed lead and defeated East Carolina 59-28 to win the East Division of Conference USA.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marshall tops E. Carolina to win division title

headlines.description: End zone D aids Akron defeat of Toledo 31-29
headlines.shortLinkText: End zone D aids Akron defeat of Toledo 31-29

events.name: Miami (OH) RedHawks at Ball State Cardinals
Bowling Green Falcons at Buffalo Bulls

headlines.description: Bowling Green will meet No. 18 Northern Illinois in the Mid-American Conference championship game after securing the MAC East division title Friday with a 24-7 win over Buffalo at Ralph Wilson Stadium.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bowling Green wins MAC East over Buffalo

events.name: Eastern Michigan Eagles at Central Michigan Chippewas

headlines.description: Central Michigan rolls past E. Michigan 42-10
headlines.shortLinkText: Central Michigan rolls past E. Michigan 42-10

events.name: Texas State Bobcats at Troy Trojans

headlines.description: Troy's bowl eligible with 42-28 win over Texas St.
headlines.shortLinkText: Troy's bowl eligible with 42-28 win over Texas St.

events.name: Florida Intl Golden Panthers at Florida Atlantic Owls

headlines.description: Stacy Coley hauled in a pair of touchdown passes and zig-zagged 73 yards on an end around for another score as Miami kept its slim hopes for a spot in the ACC title game alive with a 41-31 victory over Pittsburgh on Friday.

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Washington Huskies

headlines.description: Bishop Sankey blitzed Washington State for 139 of his 200 yards rushing in the second half to become Washington's all-time single-season rushing leader, and the Huskies reclaimed the Apple Cup with a 27-17 win over the Cougars on Friday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sankey runs Washington to Apple Cup win
